 A cargo ship has three compartments: front, middle, and rear. Their volumes and maximum allowable loads are shown in \ref{table1-24}. 
 There are three types of cargo to be shipped, with data shown in  \ref{table1-25}.

\begin{table}[h]
    \centering
    \caption{Maximum Allowable Load and Volume}
    \label{table1-24}
    \begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|}
        \hline
        \textbf{Item} & \textbf{Front Compartment} & \textbf{Middle Compartment} & \textbf{Rear Compartment} \\
        \hline
        Max Allowable Load (t) & 2000 & 3000 & 1500 \\
        \hline
        Volume ($m^3$) & 4000 & 5000 & 1500 \\
        \hline
    \end{tabular}
\end{table}

\begin{table}[h]
    \centering
    \caption{Cargo Data}
    \label{table1-25}
    \begin{tabular}{|c|c|c|c|c|}
        \hline
        \textbf{Cargo Type} & \textbf{Quantity (pieces)} & \textbf{Volume per Piece ($m^3$/piece)} & \textbf{Weight per Piece (t/piece)} & \textbf{Freight Rate (dollar/piece)} \\
        \hline
        A & 600 & 10 & 8 & 1000 \\
        \hline
        B & 1000 & 5 & 6 & 700 \\
        \hline
        C & 800 & 7 & 4 & 600 \\
        \hline
    \end{tabular}
\end{table}

 For maritime safety, the actual load weight in the front, middle, and rear compartments must maintain roughly the same proportion as their respective maximum allowable loads. 
 Specifically: The load weight ratios between the front/middle and rear/middle compartments must not deviate by more than 15\% from the ratios of their respective max allowable loads. The ratio between front and rear compartments must not deviate by more than 10\%. 
 Question: How many pieces of cargo A, B, and C should be loaded in total to maximize revenue, while meeting the volume, weight, and balance constraints? 
 Please formulate the linear programming model for this problem. 

-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Cargo_Loading_Optimization")

# Sets
cargo_types = ['A', 'B', 'C']
compartments = ['Front', 'Middle', 'Rear']

# Parameters
quantity = {'A': 600, 'B': 1000, 'C': 800}
volume_per_piece = {'A': 10, 'B': 5, 'C': 7}
weight_per_piece = {'A': 8, 'B': 6, 'C': 4}
freight_rate = {'A': 1000, 'B': 700, 'C': 600}

max_weight = {'Front': 2000, 'Middle': 3000, 'Rear': 1500}
max_volume = {'Front': 4000, 'Middle': 5000, 'Rear': 1500}

# Ratio parameters
ratio_FM = 2000 / 3000
ratio_RM = 1500 / 3000
ratio_FR = 2000 / 1500

lower_FM = 0.85 * ratio_FM
upper_FM = 1.15 * ratio_FM

lower_RM = 0.85 * ratio_RM
upper_RM = 1.15 * ratio_RM

lower_FR = 0.90 * ratio_FR
upper_FR = 1.10 * ratio_FR

# Decision variables
x = model.addVars(cargo_types, compartments, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="x")

# Objective: Maximize total revenue
model.setObjective(
    gp.quicksum(freight_rate[i] * x[i, j] for i in cargo_types for j in compartments),
    GRB.MAXIMIZE
)

# Constraints

# Quantity constraints
for i in cargo_types:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(x[i, j] for j in compartments) <= quantity[i],
        name=f"Quantity_{i}"
    )

# Volume constraints
for j in compartments:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(volume_per_piece[i] * x[i, j] for i in cargo_types) <= max_volume[j],
        name=f"Volume_{j}"
    )

# Weight constraints
for j in compartments:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(weight_per_piece[i] * x[i, j] for i in cargo_types) <= max_weight[j],
        name=f"Weight_{j}"
    )

# Compute total weight in each compartment
W_F = gp.quicksum(weight_per_piece[i] * x[i, 'Front'] for i in cargo_types)
W_M = gp.quicksum(weight_per_piece[i] * x[i, 'Middle'] for i in cargo_types)
W_R = gp.quicksum(weight_per_piece[i] * x[i, 'Rear'] for i in cargo_types)

# Balance constraints

# Front/Middle ratio
model.addConstr(W_F >= lower_FM * W_M, name="Balance_FM_Lower")
model.addConstr(W_F <= upper_FM * W_M, name="Balance_FM_Upper")

# Rear/Middle ratio
model.addConstr(W_R >= lower_RM * W_M, name="Balance_RM_Lower")
model.addConstr(W_R <= upper_RM * W_M, name="Balance_RM_Upper")

# Front/Rear ratio
model.addConstr(W_F >= lower_FR * W_R, name="Balance_FR_Lower")
model.addConstr(W_F <= upper_FR * W_R, name="Balance_FR_Upper")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal Total Revenue: {model.objVal}")
    total_loaded = {i: 0 for i in cargo_types}
    for i in cargo_types:
        for j in compartments:
            if x[i, j].x > 0:
                print(f"Cargo {i} in {j}: {x[i, j].x}")
                total_loaded[i] += x[i, j].x
    print("Total pieces loaded:")
    for i in cargo_types:
        print(f"Cargo {i}: {total_loaded[i]}")
