    A basketball team needs to select 5 players to form the starting lineup for a game. The heights and preferred positions of 8 players are shown in Table 5-11. 

\begin{table}[h]
    \centering
    \caption{Table 5-11: Player Heights and Preferred Positions}
    \renewcommand{\arraystretch}{1.2}
    \begin{tabular}{c|cccccccc}
        \toprule
        Player & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 & 5 & 6 & 7 & 8 \\
        \midrule
        Height (m) & 1.92 & 1.90 & 1.88 & 1.86 & 1.85 & 1.83 & 1.80 & 1.78 \\
        Preferred Role & Center & Center & Forward & Forward & Forward & Guard & Guard & Guard \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabular}
\end{table}

The selected lineup must satisfy the following conditions:1.Exactly one center must be selected;2.At least one forward must be selected;3.If Player 1 or Player 4 is selected, then Player 6 must also be selected; conversely, if Player 6 is selected, then neither Player 1 nor Player 4 can be selected;4.At least one of Player 2 or Player 8 must not be selected (i.e., both cannot be selected together).Question:Which 5 players should be selected to maximize the total height of the lineup? Please formulate a mathematical model to solve this problem.

-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Data
players = range(8)
heights = [1.92, 1.90, 1.88, 1.86, 1.85, 1.83, 1.80, 1.78]
roles = ["Center", "Center", "Forward", "Forward", "Forward", "Guard", "Guard", "Guard"]

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Basketball_Lineup_Selection")

# Decision variables
x = model.addVars(players, vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="x")

# Objective: Maximize total height
model.setObjective(gp.quicksum(heights[i] * x[i] for i in players), GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Constraint 1: Select exactly 5 players
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[i] for i in players) == 5, name="TotalPlayers")

# Constraint 2: Exactly one center
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[i] for i in players if roles[i] == "Center") == 1, name="OneCenter")

# Constraint 3: At least one forward
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[i] for i in players if roles[i] == "Forward") >= 1, name="AtLeastOneForward")

# Constraint 4: Logical constraints
# If Player 1 or 4 selected, then Player 6 must be selected
model.addConstr(x[0] <= x[5], name="P1_implies_P6")
model.addConstr(x[3] <= x[5], name="P4_implies_P6")

# If Player 6 selected, then neither Player 1 nor Player 4 selected
model.addConstr(x[5] + x[0] <= 1, name="P6_not_P1")
model.addConstr(x[5] + x[3] <= 1, name="P6_not_P4")

# Constraint 5: Players 2 and 8 cannot both be selected
model.addConstr(x[1] + x[7] <= 1, name="P2_P8_not_both")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Selected players:")
    for i in players:
        if x[i].x > 0.5:
            print(f"Player {i+1}, Height: {heights[i]}, Role: {roles[i]}")
    print(f"Total Height: {model.objVal}")
```
