    A company has 4 thousand yuan in capital and can invest in three projects: A, B, and C. The benefit values corresponding to different investment amounts for each project are shown in Table 7-18. How should the funds be allocated to maximize the total benefit(in thousand yuan)? Formulate and solve the mathematical model.

\begin{table}[h]
    \centering
    \caption{Benefit values for different investment amounts (Table 7-18)}
    \renewcommand{\arraystretch}{1.2}
    \begin{tabular}{c|ccccc}
        \toprule
        Project & \multicolumn{5}{c}{Investment Amount (thousand yuan)} \\
        \cmidrule(lr){2-6}
        & 0 & 1 & 2 & 3 & 4 \\
        \midrule
        A & 0 & 41 & 48 & 60 & 66 \\
        B & 0 & 42 & 50 & 60 & 66 \\
        C & 0 & 64 & 68 & 78 & 76 \\
        \bottomrule
    \end{tabular}
\end{table}

-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Data
projects = ['A', 'B', 'C']
investment_levels = [0, 1, 2, 3, 4]

benefits = {
    'A': [0, 41, 48, 60, 66],
    'B': [0, 42, 50, 60, 66],
    'C': [0, 64, 68, 78, 76]
}

total_budget = 4  # thousand yuan

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Investment_Allocation")

# Decision variables: x[p,k] = 1 if project p is invested at level k
x = model.addVars(projects, investment_levels, vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="x")

# Each project selects exactly one investment level
for p in projects:
    model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[p, k] for k in investment_levels) == 1, name=f"OneLevel_{p}")

# Total budget constraint
model.addConstr(
    gp.quicksum(k * x[p, k] for p in projects for k in investment_levels) <= total_budget,
    name="Budget"
)

# Objective: maximize total benefit
model.setObjective(
    gp.quicksum(benefits[p][k] * x[p, k] for p in projects for k in investment_levels),
    GRB.MAXIMIZE
)

# Solve model
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal Total Benefit: {model.objVal} thousand yuan")
    print("Optimal Investment Plan:")
    for p in projects:
        for k in investment_levels:
            if x[p, k].x > 0.5:
                print(f"  Project {p}: Invest {k} thousand yuan, Benefit = {benefits[p][k]}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
