  A hospital operates 24 hours a day, and the number of nurses needed in each time period is as follows: $2\!:\!00\!\sim\!6\!:\!00\!\longrightarrow\!10$ nurses, $6\!:\!00\!\sim$ 10:00\!\longrightarrow\!15$ nurses, $10:00\!\sim\!14:00\!\longrightarrow\!25$ nurses, $14:00\!\sim\!18\!:\!00\!\longrightarrow\!20$ nurses, $18\,;00\!\sim\!22\!:\!00\!\longrightarrow\!18$ nurses,$22\!:\!00\!\sim\!2\!:\!00\!-\!\!\!-\!12$ nurses. Nurses are scheduled in 6 shifts, starting at: $2:00\,,6:00\,,10:00\,,14:00\,,18:00\,,22:00$ and each nurse works 8 consecutive hours.

Task:Determine the minimum number of nurses the hospital needs to schedule in total in order to meet the staffing requirements. 

-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Time periods and required nurses
periods = ["2-6", "6-10", "10-14", "14-18", "18-22", "22-2"]
demand = [10, 15, 25, 20, 18, 12]

# Shifts starting times
shifts = ["2", "6", "10", "14", "18", "22"]

# Coverage matrix: rows = periods, columns = shifts
# 1 if shift covers period, 0 otherwise
coverage = [
    [1, 0, 0, 0, 0, 1],  # 2-6 covered by shifts starting at 2 and 22
    [1, 1, 0, 0, 0, 0],  # 6-10 covered by 2 and 6
    [0, 1, 1, 0, 0, 0],  # 10-14 covered by 6 and 10
    [0, 0, 1, 1, 0, 0],  # 14-18 covered by 10 and 14
    [0, 0, 0, 1, 1, 0],  # 18-22 covered by 14 and 18
    [0, 0, 0, 0, 1, 1],  # 22-2 covered by 18 and 22
]

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Nurse_Scheduling")

# Decision variables: number of nurses starting at each shift
x = model.addVars(len(shifts), vtype=GRB.INTEGER, lb=0, name="x")

# Objective: minimize total nurses
model.setObjective(gp.quicksum(x[j] for j in range(len(shifts))), GRB.MINIMIZE)

# Constraints: meet demand in each period
for i in range(len(periods)):
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(coverage[i][j] * x[j] for j in range(len(shifts))) >= demand[i],
        name=f"demand_{periods[i]}"
    )

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Minimum number of nurses required: {int(model.objVal)}")
    for j in range(len(shifts)):
        print(f"Nurses starting at {shifts[j]}:00 = {int(x[j].x)}")
```
