 A trading company specializes in the wholesale of a certain type of grain. The company currently has a warehouse with a capacity of 5,000 dan, and as of January 1, it has: 1,000 dan of grain in stock, 20,000 yuan in available capital, Estimated purchase and sale prices for the first quarter are shown below:  

 Table 1-8 – Grain Prices  


<html><body><table><tr><td>Month</td><td>Purchase Price (yuan/dan)</td><td>Selling Price (yuan/dan)</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>2.85</td><td>3.10</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>3.05</td><td>3.25</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>2.90</td><td>2.95</td></tr></table></body></html>  

Grain arrives in the month it is purchased, but can only be sold starting in the next month.Cash payment upon delivery. The target inventory at the end of March is 2,000 dan.

-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Grain_Trading_Optimization")

# Parameters
months = [1, 2, 3]
purchase_price = {1: 2.85, 2: 3.05, 3: 2.90}
selling_price = {1: 3.10, 2: 3.25, 3: 2.95}

warehouse_capacity = 5000
initial_inventory = 1000
initial_cash = 20000
target_inventory_end = 2000

# Decision variables
purchase = model.addVars(months, name="Purchase", lb=0)
sell = model.addVars(months, name="Sell", lb=0)
inventory = model.addVars(months, name="Inventory", lb=0)
cash = model.addVars(months, name="Cash", lb=0)

# Inventory balance constraints
for m in months:
    if m == 1:
        model.addConstr(inventory[m] == initial_inventory + purchase[m] - sell[m], name=f"InvBalance_{m}")
    else:
        model.addConstr(inventory[m] == inventory[m-1] + purchase[m] - sell[m], name=f"InvBalance_{m}")

# Sales constraint (can only sell from previous month's inventory)
model.addConstr(sell[1] == 0, name="SellMonth1")

for m in [2, 3]:
    if m == 2:
        model.addConstr(sell[m] <= initial_inventory + purchase[1], name=f"SellLimit_{m}")
    else:
        model.addConstr(sell[m] <= inventory[m-1], name=f"SellLimit_{m}")

# Warehouse capacity constraints
for m in months:
    model.addConstr(inventory[m] <= warehouse_capacity, name=f"Capacity_{m}")

# Cash balance constraints
for m in months:
    if m == 1:
        model.addConstr(
            cash[m] == initial_cash - purchase_price[m] * purchase[m] + selling_price[m] * sell[m],
            name=f"CashBalance_{m}"
        )
    else:
        model.addConstr(
            cash[m] == cash[m-1] - purchase_price[m] * purchase[m] + selling_price[m] * sell[m],
            name=f"CashBalance_{m}"
        )

# Cash availability constraints (cannot spend more than available cash)
for m in months:
    if m == 1:
        model.addConstr(purchase_price[m] * purchase[m] <= initial_cash, name=f"CashLimit_{m}")
    else:
        model.addConstr(purchase_price[m] * purchase[m] <= cash[m-1], name=f"CashLimit_{m}")

# Target ending inventory
model.addConstr(inventory[3] == target_inventory_end, name="EndingInventory")

# Objective: Maximize final cash
model.setObjective(cash[3], GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Solution Found:")
    for m in months:
        print(f"Month {m}:")
        print(f"  Purchase = {purchase[m].X:.2f} dan")
        print(f"  Sell     = {sell[m].X:.2f} dan")
        print(f"  Inventory= {inventory[m].X:.2f} dan")
        print(f"  Cash     = {cash[m].X:.2f} yuan")
    print(f"Final Cash: {cash[3].X:.2f} yuan")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
