1.33 A farm has 100 hectares (hm²) of land and 15,000 yuan of funds available for production development. The farm has 3,500 person-days of labor in autumn and winter, and 4,000 person-days in spring and summer. If the labor is not fully used, workers can go out to work; the wage income in spring and summer is 2.1 yuan/person-day, and in autumn and winter is 1.8 yuan/person-day.The farm grows three types of crops: soybeans, corn, and wheat, and raises dairy cows and chickens.When planting crops, no special investment is needed. When raising animals:Each dairy cow requires an investment of 400 yuan,Each chicken requires an investment of 3 yuan. Each dairy cow also requires 1.5 hm² of land for forage planting, and labor: 100 person-days in autumn and winter, 50 person-days in spring and summer, Annual net income is 400 yuan per cow.Chickens do not occupy land, but require labor:0.6 person-days per chicken in autumn and winter,0.3 person-days per chicken in spring and summer,Annual net income is 2 yuan per chicken.The current chicken house allows a maximum of 3,000 chickens to be raised, and the cowshed allows a maximum of 32 dairy cows.The labor required and income from the three crops are shown in Table 1-9.  

Table 1-9  


<html><body><table><tr><td>Item</td><td>Soybeans</td><td>Corn</td><td>Wheat</td></tr><tr><td>Autumn and Winter labor (person-days)</td><td>20</td><td>35</td><td>10</td></tr><tr><td>Spring and Summer labor (person-days)</td><td>50</td><td>75</td><td>40</td></tr><tr><td>Annual net income (yuan/hm²)</td><td>175</td><td>300</td><td>120</td></tr></table></body></html>  

Try to determine the farm’s operational plan that will maximize annual net income.

-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Farm_Optimization")

# Decision variables
soy = model.addVar(lb=0, name="Soybeans_hm2")
corn = model.addVar(lb=0, name="Corn_hm2")
wheat = model.addVar(lb=0, name="Wheat_hm2")

cows = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=32, name="Dairy_Cows")
chickens = model.addVar(lb=0, ub=3000, name="Chickens")

labor_AW_out = model.addVar(lb=0, name="Labor_AutumnWinter_Out")
labor_SS_out = model.addVar(lb=0, name="Labor_SpringSummer_Out")

# Land constraint
model.addConstr(
    soy + corn + wheat + 1.5 * cows <= 100,
    name="Land"
)

# Capital constraint
model.addConstr(
    400 * cows + 3 * chickens <= 15000,
    name="Capital"
)

# Autumn and Winter labor constraint
model.addConstr(
    20 * soy + 35 * corn + 10 * wheat + 100 * cows + 0.6 * chickens + labor_AW_out == 3500,
    name="Labor_AutumnWinter"
)

# Spring and Summer labor constraint
model.addConstr(
    50 * soy + 75 * corn + 40 * wheat + 50 * cows + 0.3 * chickens + labor_SS_out == 4000,
    name="Labor_SpringSummer"
)

# Objective function
model.setObjective(
    175 * soy + 300 * corn + 120 * wheat
    + 400 * cows + 2 * chickens
    + 1.8 * labor_AW_out + 2.1 * labor_SS_out,
    GRB.MAXIMIZE
)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal Annual Net Income: {model.objVal:.2f} yuan")
    for v in model.getVars():
        print(f"{v.varName}: {v.x:.2f}")
