1.42 A timber storage and transportation company has a large warehouse used for storing and selling timber. Due to seasonal price fluctuations of timber, the company purchases timber at the beginning of each quarter. A portion is sold during the current quarter, and another portion is stored for sale in later quarters. It is known that the company’s warehouse has a maximum timber storage capacity of 20 thousand m³, and the storage cost is (a + b u) yuan per m³, where a = 70, b = 100, and u is the storage time in quarters. The purchase prices, selling prices, and estimated maximum sales volumes per quarter are given in Table 1-18. 

 Table 1-18  


<html><body><table><tr><td>Quarter</td><td>Purchase Price (thousand yuan per thousand m³)</td><td>Selling Price (thousand yuan per thousand m³)</td><td>Estimated Max Sales Volume (thousand m³)</td></tr><tr><td>Winter</td><td>410</td><td>425</td><td>100</td></tr><tr><td>Spring</td><td>430</td><td>440</td><td>140</td></tr><tr><td>Summer</td><td>460</td><td>465</td><td>200</td></tr><tr><td>Autumn</td><td>450</td><td>455</td><td>160</td></tr></table></body></html>  

Because timber is not suitable for long-term storage, all stored timber must be sold by the end of autumn each year. Task: Formulate a linear programming model for this problem in order to maximize the company’s annual profit(in thousand yuan).  

-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB, quicksum

# Data
quarters = ["Winter", "Spring", "Summer", "Autumn"]
purchase_price = {
    "Winter": 410,
    "Spring": 430,
    "Summer": 460,
    "Autumn": 450
}
selling_price = {
    "Winter": 425,
    "Spring": 440,
    "Summer": 465,
    "Autumn": 455
}
max_sales = {
    "Winter": 100,
    "Spring": 140,
    "Summer": 200,
    "Autumn": 160
}

capacity = 20  # thousand m^3
a = 70
b = 100

# Model
model = Model("Timber_Storage_Planning")

# Decision variables
# x[i,j]: amount purchased in quarter i and sold in quarter j (i <= j)
x = {}
for i in range(4):
    for j in range(i, 4):
        x[i, j] = model.addVar(lb=0, name=f"x_{quarters[i]}_{quarters[j]}")

model.update()

# Objective function: maximize total profit
profit = quicksum(
    (selling_price[quarters[j]] - purchase_price[quarters[i]] - (a + b * (j - i)) * (j - i)) * x[i, j]
    for i in range(4) for j in range(i, 4)
)

model.setObjective(profit, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Constraints

# 1. Sales volume constraints
for j in range(4):
    model.addConstr(
        quicksum(x[i, j] for i in range(j + 1)) <= max_sales[quarters[j]],
        name=f"Sales_Limit_{quarters[j]}"
    )

# 2. Storage capacity constraints (inventory at end of each quarter)
for t in range(4):
    inventory = quicksum(
        x[i, j]
        for i in range(t + 1)
        for j in range(max(i, t + 1), 4)
    )
    model.addConstr(inventory <= capacity, name=f"Storage_Capacity_End_{quarters[t]}")

# 3. All timber sold by end of Autumn (no inventory after Autumn)
# (Automatically satisfied since no j > 3, but enforce explicitly)
model.addConstr(
    quicksum(
        x[i, j]
        for i in range(4)
        for j in range(i, 4)
        if j > 3
    ) == 0,
    name="No_Ending_Inventory"
)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Maximum Annual Profit: {model.objVal:.2f} thousand yuan")
    for i in range(4):
        for j in range(i, 4):
            if x[i, j].x > 1e-6:
                print(f"Purchase in {quarters[i]}, Sell in {quarters[j]}: {x[i, j].x:.2f} thousand m^3")
