1.47he Hongsheng Factory produces three types of products: I, II, and III, each of which undergoes two processing stages, A and B. Stage A has two machines $\mathbf{A}_{1}$ 、$\mathbf{A}_{2}$ , Stage B has three machines $\mathrm{B}_{1},\mathrm{B}_{2},\mathrm{B}_{3}$ .The processing rules are: Product I can be processed on any machine in both stages A and B;Product II can be processed on any A machine, but in stage B it can only be processed on machine $\mathbf{B}_{2}$; Product III can only be processed on $\mathbf{A}_{2}$  and $\mathbf{B}_{2}$ , The processing time required per unit, machine available time, processing cost, and other relevant data are shown in Table 1-20.Question:How should the production plan be arranged in order to maximize the factory’s profit?  

Table 1-20  


<html><body><table><tr><td rowspan="2">Machine</td><td colspan="3">Product</td><td rowspan="2">Available Hours</td><td rowspan="2">Processing Cost (yuan/h)</td></tr><tr><td>I</td><td>Ⅱ</td><td>Ⅲ</td></tr><tr><td>A1</td><td>5</td><td>10</td><td></td><td>6 000</td><td>0.05</td></tr><tr><td>A2</td><td>7</td><td>9</td><td>12</td><td>10 000</td><td>0.03</td></tr><tr><td>B1</td><td>6</td><td>8</td><td></td><td>4.000</td><td>0.06</td></tr><tr><td>B2</td><td>4</td><td></td><td>11</td><td>7000</td><td>0.11</td></tr><tr><td>B3</td><td>7</td><td></td><td></td><td>4 000</td><td>0.05</td></tr><tr><td>Raw material cost (yuan/unit)</td><td>0.25</td><td>0.35</td><td>0.50</td><td></td><td></td></tr><tr><td>Selling price (yuan/unit)</td><td>1.25</td><td>2.00</td><td>2.80</td><td></td><td></td></tr></table></body></html>  


-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Hongsheng_Factory_Production")

# Sets
products = ["I", "II", "III"]
machines_A = ["A1", "A2"]
machines_B = ["B1", "B2", "B3"]
machines = machines_A + machines_B

# Processing time (hours per unit), only for allowed combinations
proc_time = {
    ("A1","I"):5,   ("A1","II"):10,
    ("A2","I"):7,   ("A2","II"):9,   ("A2","III"):12,
    ("B1","I"):6,
    ("B2","I"):4,   ("B2","II"):8,   ("B2","III"):11,
    ("B3","I"):7
}

# Machine available hours
avail_hours = {
    "A1":6000,
    "A2":10000,
    "B1":4000,
    "B2":7000,
    "B3":4000
}

# Processing cost (yuan per hour)
proc_cost = {
    "A1":0.05,
    "A2":0.03,
    "B1":0.06,
    "B2":0.11,
    "B3":0.05
}

# Raw material cost (yuan per unit)
raw_cost = {
    "I":0.25,
    "II":0.35,
    "III":0.50
}

# Selling price (yuan per unit)
sell_price = {
    "I":1.25,
    "II":2.00,
    "III":2.80
}

# Decision variables: quantity processed on machine m for product p
x = model.addVars(proc_time.keys(), name="x", lb=0)

# Production quantity variables
q = model.addVars(products, name="q", lb=0)

# Stage A flow balance
for p in products:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(x[m,p] for m in machines_A if (m,p) in proc_time) == q[p],
        name=f"StageA_balance_{p}"
    )

# Stage B flow balance
for p in products:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(x[m,p] for m in machines_B if (m,p) in proc_time) == q[p],
        name=f"StageB_balance_{p}"
    )

# Machine capacity constraints
for m in machines:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(proc_time[m,p] * x[m,p] for p in products if (m,p) in proc_time) 
        <= avail_hours[m],
        name=f"Capacity_{m}"
    )

# Objective: maximize profit
revenue = gp.quicksum(sell_price[p] * q[p] for p in products)
raw_material = gp.quicksum(raw_cost[p] * q[p] for p in products)
processing = gp.quicksum(proc_time[m,p] * proc_cost[m] * x[m,p] for (m,p) in proc_time)

model.setObjective(revenue - raw_material - processing, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Solve
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Maximum Profit: {model.objVal:.4f}")
    for p in products:
        print(f"Production of Product {p}: {q[p].x:.4f}")
    for (m,p) in proc_time:
        if x[m,p].x > 1e-6:
            print(f"Units of Product {p} processed on {m}: {x[m,p].x:.4f}")
```
