3.13 In the transportation problem shown in Table 3-17, if one unit of goods from origin i is not shipped, a storage cost will be incurred. Assume that the unit storage costs at origins 1, 2, and 3 are 5, 4, and 3, respectively. Also, it is assumed that at least 38 units must be shipped from origin 2 and at least 27 units from origin 3. Solve for the optimal solution to this transportation problem.  

 Table 3-17  


<html><body><table><tr><td>Origin/Destination</td><td>A</td><td>B</td><td>C</td><td>Supply</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>2</td><td>20</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>1</td><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>40</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>3</td><td>30</td></tr><tr><td>Demand</td><td>30</td><td>20</td><td>20</td><td></td></tr></table></body></html>  


-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Sets
origins = [1, 2, 3]
destinations = ['A', 'B', 'C']

# Data
supply = {1: 20, 2: 40, 3: 30}
demand = {'A': 30, 'B': 20, 'C': 20}

cost = {
    (1, 'A'): 1, (1, 'B'): 2, (1, 'C'): 2,
    (2, 'A'): 1, (2, 'B'): 4, (2, 'C'): 5,
    (3, 'A'): 2, (3, 'B'): 3, (3, 'C'): 3
}

storage_cost = {1: 5, 2: 4, 3: 3}

# Model
model = gp.Model("Transportation_with_Storage")

# Decision variables
x = model.addVars(origins, destinations, name="x", lb=0)
s = model.addVars(origins, name="storage", lb=0)

# Objective function
model.setObjective(
    gp.quicksum(cost[i, j] * x[i, j] for i in origins for j in destinations) +
    gp.quicksum(storage_cost[i] * s[i] for i in origins),
    GRB.MINIMIZE
)

# Supply constraints (including storage)
for i in origins:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(x[i, j] for j in destinations) + s[i] == supply[i],
        name=f"supply_{i}"
    )

# Demand constraints
for j in destinations:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(x[i, j] for i in origins) == demand[j],
        name=f"demand_{j}"
    )

# Minimum shipment constraints
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[2, j] for j in destinations) >= 38, name="min_ship_2")
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[3, j] for j in destinations) >= 27, name="min_ship_3")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal Objective Value: {model.objVal}\n")
    print("Shipping Plan:")
    for i in origins:
        for j in destinations:
            if x[i, j].x > 1e-6:
                print(f"x[{i},{j}] = {x[i,j].x}")
    print("\nStorage:")
    for i in origins:
        if s[i].x > 1e-6:
            print(f"storage[{i}] = {s[i].x}")
