5.19 A certain product can be processed on any one of four machines: A, B, C, or D. The setup cost, unit production cost, and maximum production capacity for each machine are shown in Table 5-7.The factory needs to produce 2,000 units of the product.Question: How should production be allocated among the machines to minimize the total cost? Formulate the mathematical model.  

Table 5-7  


<html><body><table><tr><td>Machine</td><td>Setup Cost (Yuan)</td><td>Unit Cost (Yuan/unit)</td><td>Max Capacity (units)</td></tr><tr><td>A</td><td>1000</td><td>20</td><td>900</td></tr><tr><td>B</td><td>920</td><td>24</td><td>1 000</td></tr><tr><td>C</td><td>800</td><td>16</td><td>1 200</td></tr><tr><td>D</td><td>700</td><td>28</td><td>1 600</td></tr></table></body></html> 


-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 **Mathematical Model**

Decision Variables  
\( x_i \) = production quantity on machine \( i \) (units), \( i \in \{A,B,C,D\} \)  
\( y_i \) = 1 if machine \( i \) is used; 0 otherwise  

Parameters  

| Machine | Setup Cost \(f_i\) | Unit Cost \(c_i\) | Capacity \(u_i\) |
|----------|------------------|----------------|----------------|
| A | 1000 | 20 | 900 |
| B | 920 | 24 | 1000 |
| C | 800 | 16 | 1200 |
| D | 700 | 28 | 1600 |

Demand: \( D = 2000 \)

Objective Function  

\[
\min Z = \sum_{i} (f_i y_i + c_i x_i)
\]

Subject to  

\[
\sum_{i} x_i = 2000
\]

\[
x_i \le u_i y_i \quad \forall i
\]

\[
x_i \ge 0 \quad \forall i
\]

\[
y_i \in \{0,1\} \quad \forall i
\]

