5.24 The Hongdou Garment Factory uses three types of specialized equipment to produce shirts, T-shirts, and casual wear, respectively. The labor requirement, material usage, selling price, and variable cost per unit for each of the three products are shown in Table 5-10.  

 Table 5-10  


<html><body><table><tr><td>Product</td><td>Labor per Unit</td><td>Material per Unit</td><td>Selling Price</td><td>Variable Cost</td></tr><tr><td>Shirt</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>120</td><td>60</td></tr><tr><td>T-shirt</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>80</td><td>40</td></tr><tr><td>Casual Wear</td><td>6</td><td>6</td><td>180</td><td>80</td></tr></table></body></html>  

 The factory has a weekly availability of 150 labor units and 160 material units. The weekly fixed costs for operating the specialized equipment for producing shirts, T-shirts, and casual wear are 2,000, 1,500, and 1,000 respectively.Requirement: Design a weekly production plan for the factory that maximizes profit. 

-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Hongdou_Garment_Production")

# Decision variables
x1 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Shirts", lb=0)
x2 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="Tshirts", lb=0)
x3 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.CONTINUOUS, name="CasualWear", lb=0)

y1 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="Produce_Shirts")
y2 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="Produce_Tshirts")
y3 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="Produce_CasualWear")

# Big-M values (maximum possible production based on resources)
M1 = 40      # Shirts
M2 = 53.33   # T-shirts
M3 = 25      # Casual Wear

# Resource constraints
model.addConstr(3*x1 + 2*x2 + 6*x3 <= 150, name="Labor")
model.addConstr(4*x1 + 3*x2 + 6*x3 <= 160, name="Material")

# Linking constraints
model.addConstr(x1 <= M1 * y1, name="Link_Shirts")
model.addConstr(x2 <= M2 * y2, name="Link_Tshirts")
model.addConstr(x3 <= M3 * y3, name="Link_CasualWear")

# Objective function (maximize profit)
profit = (
    60 * x1 +    # (120 - 60) * Shirts
    40 * x2 +    # (80 - 40) * T-shirts
    100 * x3     # (180 - 80) * Casual Wear
    - 2000 * y1
    - 1500 * y2
    - 1000 * y3
)

model.setObjective(profit, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Weekly Production Plan:")
    print(f"Shirts: {x1.X:.2f}")
    print(f"T-shirts: {x2.X:.2f}")
    print(f"Casual Wear: {x3.X:.2f}")
    print(f"Maximum Profit: {model.objVal:.2f}")
```
