5.26 The Hongxing Plastics Factory produces six types of plastic containers. The capacity, demand, and variable cost for each type of container are shown in Table 5-11.  

 Table 5-11  


<html><body><table><tr><td>Container ID</td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>6</td></tr><tr><td>Capacity (cm³)</td><td>1500</td><td>2500</td><td>4000</td><td>6000</td><td>9000</td><td>12000</td></tr><tr><td>Demand (units)</td><td>500</td><td>550</td><td>700</td><td>900</td><td>400</td><td>300</td></tr><tr><td>Variable Cost (Yuan/unit)</td><td>5</td><td>8</td><td>10</td><td>12</td><td>16</td><td>18</td></tr></table></body></html>  

 Each container type is produced by a different dedicated machine, and the fixed cost for each machine is 1,200 Yuan. When the quantity of a certain container type cannot meet the demand, containers with larger capacities may be used as substitutes.Question: How should production be organized to minimize the total cost, while satisfying the demand? 


-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Data
types = range(6)
capacity = [1500, 2500, 4000, 6000, 9000, 12000]
demand = [500, 550, 700, 900, 400, 300]
var_cost = [5, 8, 10, 12, 16, 18]
fixed_cost = 1200

# Model
model = gp.Model("Hongxing_Plastics_Production")

# Decision variables
x = model.addVars(types, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="Production")
y = model.addVars(types, vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="MachineUse")
a = model.addVars(types, types, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="Allocation")

# Big M
M = sum(demand)

# Constraints

# Production equals allocation
for i in types:
    model.addConstr(
        x[i] == gp.quicksum(a[i, k] for k in types if k <= i),
        name=f"ProdAlloc_{i}"
    )

# Demand satisfaction (larger containers can substitute smaller ones)
for k in types:
    model.addConstr(
        gp.quicksum(a[i, k] for i in types if i >= k) >= demand[k],
        name=f"Demand_{k}"
    )

# Allocation only allowed if capacity is sufficient
for i in types:
    for k in types:
        if i < k:
            model.addConstr(a[i, k] == 0, name=f"InfeasibleAlloc_{i}_{k}")

# Link production and machine usage
for i in types:
    model.addConstr(x[i] <= M * y[i], name=f"BigM_{i}")

# Objective: Minimize total cost
model.setObjective(
    gp.quicksum(var_cost[i] * x[i] + fixed_cost * y[i] for i in types),
    GRB.MINIMIZE
)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print(f"Optimal Total Cost: {model.objVal:.2f} Yuan\n")
    print("Production Plan:")
    for i in types:
        if x[i].x > 0:
            print(f"Container Type {i+1}: Produce {int(x[i].x)} units")
    print("\nMachine Usage:")
    for i in types:
        print(f"Machine {i+1}: {'Used' if y[i].x > 0.5 else 'Not Used'}")
    print("\nAllocation Plan:")
    for i in types:
        for k in types:
            if a[i, k].x > 0:
                print(f"Type {i+1} used to satisfy Demand of Type {k+1}: {int(a[i, k].x)} units")
