5.30 Hanguang Automobile Manufacturing Plant produces three brands of automobiles: Zhujiang, Songhuajiang, and Huanghe. The steel and labor required to produce one unit of each brand, as well as the expected profit, are shown in Table 5-13. The available monthly steel and labor hours are also given.  

 Table 5-13  


| Item       | Zhujiang    | Songhuajiang   | Huanghe    | Monthly Availability   |
| -------- | ----- | ----- | ----- | ------- |
| Steel (tons)   | 1.5   | 3.0   | 5.0   | 6 000   |
| Labor (hours)  | 300   | 250   | 400   | 600 000 |
| Expected Profit (Yuan) | 2 000 | 3 000 | 4 000 |         |


 It is known that the economic production batch size for each of these automobiles is at least 1,000 units per month. That is, the monthly output of each brand must either be greater than 1,000 units or not produced at all. Task: Determine a production plan for the factory that maximizes total profit under the above constraints. 


-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Hanguang_Automobile_Production")

# Upper bounds based on resource limits
max_zhujiang = 2000
max_songhuajiang = 2000
max_huanghe = 1200

# Decision variables
x1 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.INTEGER, lb=0, ub=max_zhujiang, name="Zhujiang")
x2 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.INTEGER, lb=0, ub=max_songhuajiang, name="Songhuajiang")
x3 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.INTEGER, lb=0, ub=max_huanghe, name="Huanghe")

y1 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="Produce_Zhujiang")
y2 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="Produce_Songhuajiang")
y3 = model.addVar(vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="Produce_Huanghe")

# Resource constraints
model.addConstr(1.5*x1 + 3.0*x2 + 5.0*x3 <= 6000, name="Steel")
model.addConstr(300*x1 + 250*x2 + 400*x3 <= 600000, name="Labor")

# Minimum batch size constraints (either 0 or at least 1000)
model.addConstr(x1 >= 1000*y1, name="MinBatch_Zhujiang")
model.addConstr(x2 >= 1000*y2, name="MinBatch_Songhuajiang")
model.addConstr(x3 >= 1000*y3, name="MinBatch_Huanghe")

# Linking upper bounds with binary variables
model.addConstr(x1 <= max_zhujiang*y1, name="MaxLink_Zhujiang")
model.addConstr(x2 <= max_songhuajiang*y2, name="MaxLink_Songhuajiang")
model.addConstr(x3 <= max_huanghe*y3, name="MaxLink_Huanghe")

# Objective function
model.setObjective(2000*x1 + 3000*x2 + 4000*x3, GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Production Plan:")
    print(f"Zhujiang: {x1.X} units")
    print(f"Songhuajiang: {x2.X} units")
    print(f"Huanghe: {x3.X} units")
    print(f"Maximum Profit: {model.objVal} Yuan")
```
