5.31 Tuanjie Township consists of 8 villages. The coordinates of each village and the number of primary school students are shown in Table 5-14.  

Table 5-14  


<html><body><table><tr><td rowspan="2">Village ID</td><td colspan="2">Coordinates</td><td rowspan="2">Number of Students</td></tr><tr><td>x</td><td>y</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>0</td><td>0</td><td>60</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>10</td><td>3</td><td>80</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>12</td><td>15</td><td>100</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>14</td><td>13</td><td>120</td></tr><tr><td>5</td><td>16</td><td>9</td><td>80</td></tr><tr><td>6</td><td>18</td><td>6</td><td>60</td></tr><tr><td>7</td><td>8</td><td>12</td><td>40</td></tr><tr><td>8</td><td>6</td><td>10</td><td>80</td></tr></table></body></html>  

 Considering economies of scale, it is planned to build one primary school in each of two villages. Question: In which two villages should the schools be built to minimize the total walking distance for all primary school students? (Walking distance is calculated using Euclidean distance between villages.) 


-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB
import math

# Data
villages = {
    1: (0, 0, 60),
    2: (10, 3, 80),
    3: (12, 15, 100),
    4: (14, 13, 120),
    5: (16, 9, 80),
    6: (18, 6, 60),
    7: (8, 12, 40),
    8: (6, 10, 80)
}

V = list(villages.keys())
p = 2  # number of schools to build

# Compute Euclidean distances
dist = {}
for i in V:
    xi, yi, _ = villages[i]
    for j in V:
        xj, yj, _ = villages[j]
        dist[i, j] = math.hypot(xi - xj, yi - yj)

# Model
model = gp.Model("p_median_school_location")

# Decision variables
y = model.addVars(V, vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="y")  # 1 if school built in village j
x = model.addVars(V, V, vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="x")  # 1 if village i assigned to school j

# Objective: minimize total weighted walking distance
model.setObjective(
    gp.quicksum(
        villages[i][2] * dist[i, j] * x[i, j]
        for i in V for j in V
    ),
    GRB.MINIMIZE
)

# Constraints

# Each village assigned to exactly one school
for i in V:
    model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(x[i, j] for j in V) == 1, name=f"assign_{i}")

# Assignment only to open schools
for i in V:
    for j in V:
        model.addConstr(x[i, j] <= y[j], name=f"open_link_{i}_{j}")

# Exactly p schools opened
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(y[j] for j in V) == p, name="num_schools")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal total walking distance:", model.objVal)
    print("Schools should be built in villages:")
    for j in V:
        if y[j].x > 0.5:
            print(f"Village {j}")
    print("\nAssignment of villages to schools:")
    for i in V:
        for j in V:
            if x[i, j].x > 0.5:
                print(f"Village {i} assigned to Village {j}")
