  A factory produces three types of products. The weight and profit of each product are shown in Table 7-8. These products are to be shipped to the market for sale, and the total transportation capacity cannot exceed 10 tons.  

  Table 7-8  


  <html><body><table><tr><td>Product Type</td><td>Weight (t/piece)</td><td>Profit (yuan/piece)</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>100</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>140</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>180</td></tr></table></body></html>  


-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB

# Create model
model = Model("Factory_Transportation_Optimization")

# Data
weights = [2, 3, 4]      # weight per piece (tons)
profits = [100, 140, 180]  # profit per piece (yuan)
capacity = 10            # total transportation capacity (tons)
n = 3                    # number of product types

# Decision variables: number of pieces for each product type (integer, >= 0)
x = model.addVars(n, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="x", lb=0)

# Objective function: maximize total profit
model.setObjective(sum(profits[i] * x[i] for i in range(n)), GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Constraint: total weight cannot exceed capacity
model.addConstr(sum(weights[i] * x[i] for i in range(n)) <= capacity, name="WeightConstraint")

# Optimize model
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Solution Found:")
    for i in range(n):
        print(f"Number of Product {i+1}: {int(x[i].x)}")
    print(f"Maximum Profit: {model.objVal}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
