  There is a truck available for transporting cargo, and there are 4 types of goods that can be transported with it. The weight, volume, and value of each type of good are shown in Table 7-9.  

  Table 7-9  


  <html><body><table><tr><td>Item ID</td><td>Weight (t)</td><td>Volume (m³)</td><td>Value (thousand yuan)</td></tr><tr><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>2</td><td>3</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>2</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>4</td><td>2</td><td>5</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>5</td><td>3</td><td>6</td></tr></table></body></html>  

  The truck has a maximum weight capacity of 15 tons and a maximum volume capacity of 10 cubic meters. Under these constraints, there is no limit on the number of items of each type that can be loaded. Question: How should the four types of goods be combined to maximize the total value of the cargo per truckload?  


-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Data
items = [1, 2, 3, 4]
weight = {1: 2, 2: 3, 3: 4, 4: 5}
volume = {1: 2, 2: 2, 3: 2, 4: 3}
value = {1: 3, 2: 4, 3: 5, 4: 6}

max_weight = 15
max_volume = 10

# Create model
model = gp.Model("Truck_Loading_Problem")

# Decision variables: number of each item (integer, no upper bound)
x = model.addVars(items, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, lb=0, name="x")

# Objective: maximize total value
model.setObjective(gp.quicksum(value[i] * x[i] for i in items), GRB.MAXIMIZE)

# Weight constraint
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(weight[i] * x[i] for i in items) <= max_weight, name="WeightConstraint")

# Volume constraint
model.addConstr(gp.quicksum(volume[i] * x[i] for i in items) <= max_volume, name="VolumeConstraint")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal total value (thousand yuan):", model.objVal)
    for i in items:
        print(f"Number of item {i} loaded:", int(x[i].x))
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
