  A security department has 12 patrol units responsible for patrolling 4 warehouses. According to regulations, 2 to 4 patrol units can be assigned to each warehouse.Due to the differences in the number of patrol units assigned, the expected number of accidents per year for each warehouse varies, as shown in Table 7-11. Question: Use dynamic programming to determine how many patrol units should be assigned to each warehouse in order to minimize the total expected number of accidents.  

  Table 7-11  


  <html><body><table><tr><td>Patrol Units \ Warehouse </td><td>1</td><td>2</td><td>3</td><td>4</td></tr><tr><td>2</td><td>18</td><td>38</td><td>14</td><td>34</td></tr><tr><td>3</td><td>16</td><td>36</td><td>12</td><td>31</td></tr><tr><td>4</td><td>12</td><td>30</td><td>11</td><td>25</td></tr></table></body></html>


-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
from gurobipy import Model, GRB, quicksum

# Data
warehouses = [1, 2, 3, 4]
units_options = [2, 3, 4]

# Expected accidents table
accidents = {
    (1, 2): 18, (1, 3): 16, (1, 4): 12,
    (2, 2): 38, (2, 3): 36, (2, 4): 30,
    (3, 2): 14, (3, 3): 12, (3, 4): 11,
    (4, 2): 34, (4, 3): 31, (4, 4): 25
}

total_units = 12

# Create model
model = Model("Patrol_Allocation")

# Decision variables: x[w,u] = 1 if warehouse w assigned u patrol units
x = model.addVars(warehouses, units_options, vtype=GRB.BINARY, name="x")

# Each warehouse must be assigned exactly one patrol level
for w in warehouses:
    model.addConstr(quicksum(x[w, u] for u in units_options) == 1)

# Total patrol units constraint
model.addConstr(
    quicksum(u * x[w, u] for w in warehouses for u in units_options) == total_units
)

# Objective: Minimize total expected accidents
model.setObjective(
    quicksum(accidents[w, u] * x[w, u] for w in warehouses for u in units_options),
    GRB.MINIMIZE
)

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
    print("Optimal Allocation:")
    for w in warehouses:
        for u in units_options:
            if x[w, u].x > 0.5:
                print(f"Warehouse {w}: {u} patrol units")
    print(f"Minimum Total Expected Accidents: {model.objVal}")
else:
    print("No optimal solution found.")
```
