  Changzheng Hospital is a district-level hospital in Changning District. The number of on-duty nurses required in each time period of the day is shown in Table C-2.  

  Table C-2  


  <html><body><table><tr><td>Time Period</td><td>6:00--10:00</td><td>10:0--14:00</td><td>14:00--18:00</td><td>18:00--22:00</td><td>22：00--6：00（次日）</td></tr><tr><td>Required Number of Nurses</td><td>18</td><td>20</td><td>19</td><td>17</td><td>12</td></tr></table></body></html>  

  The hospital organizes nurses into five shifts, each 8 hours long. The specific shift times are as follows: Shift 1: 2:00–10:00, Shift 2: 6:00–14:00, Shift 3: 10:00–18:00, Shift 4: 14:00–22:00,Shift 5: 18:00–2:00 (next day), Each nurse works 5 shifts per week, scheduled on different days. A head nurse is in charge of creating the duty schedule. The scheduling plan must be personnel- or cost-efficient, while also being reasonable and practical. The following is a plan under consideration: Plan 1: Each nurse works 5 consecutive days, followed by 2 days off, and works a different shift each day, cycling through Shift 1 to Shift 5 in sequence. For example:,If a nurse starts on Monday, she works:Shift 1 on Monday,Shift 2 on Tuesday,…,Shift 5 on Friday; Another nurse starting on Wednesday would work: Shift 1 on Wednesday,…,Shift 5 on Sunday. Question: How can we minimize the total number of nurses required under Plan 1? 


-------------
【Python Gurobi 代码】:
 ```python
import gurobipy as gp
from gurobipy import GRB

# Sets
days = range(7)  # 0=Mon,1=Tue,...,6=Sun
periods = range(5)  # 0:6-10,1:10-14,2:14-18,3:18-22,4:22-6

# Required nurses per period (same each day)
demand = {
    0: 18,  # 6:00-10:00
    1: 20,  # 10:00-14:00
    2: 19,  # 14:00-18:00
    3: 17,  # 18:00-22:00
    4: 12   # 22:00-6:00
}

# Shift coverage matrix: shift s covers which periods
# Shifts: 0:2-10,1:6-14,2:10-18,3:14-22,4:18-2
shift_cover = {
    0: [0],        # 2-10 covers 6-10
    1: [0,1],      # 6-14 covers 6-10,10-14
    2: [1,2],      # 10-18 covers 10-14,14-18
    3: [2,3],      # 14-22 covers 14-18,18-22
    4: [3,4]       # 18-2 covers 18-22,22-6
}

# Model
model = gp.Model("Nurse_Scheduling_Plan1")

# Decision variables
# x[d]: number of nurses starting their 5-day cycle on day d
x = model.addVars(days, vtype=GRB.INTEGER, name="x")

# Objective: minimize total number of nurses
model.setObjective(gp.quicksum(x[d] for d in days), GRB.MINIMIZE)

# Coverage constraints
for d in days:  # each day
    for p in periods:  # each time period
        coverage = gp.LinExpr()
        for s in days:  # start day of nurse
            # Check if nurse starting on day s works on day d
            diff = (d - s) % 7
            if diff <= 4:  # works 5 consecutive days
                shift = diff  # shift index 0-4
                if p in shift_cover[shift]:
                    coverage += x[s]
        model.addConstr(coverage >= demand[p], name=f"cover_day{d}_period{p}")

# Optimize
model.optimize()

# Output results
if model.status == GRB.OPTIMAL:
